step.reason:
\begin{align}
I &= \int x. \log x.dx\\
&= \log x \int x.dx - \int \left[\dfrac{d}{dx}\log x \int x.dx\right].dx\\
&= \log x . \dfrac{x^2}{2} - \int \dfrac{1}{x}.\dfrac{x^2}{2}.dx\\
&= \log x . \dfrac{x^2}{2} - \dfrac{1}{2}\int x.dx = \dfrac{x^2}{2} \log x - \dfrac{x^2}{4}+ C\\
\end{align}
